Now that the structures are in place, we need to swap out the {THING:CircuitboardAirlockControl} for the {THING:CircuitboardAdvAirlockControl} 

There are a few differences when programming the {THING:CircuitboardAdvAirlockControl}. Firstly, you need to select an internal and external {THING:StructureActiveVent}. Unlike doors, you will need to look at the switch on the {THING:StructureActiveVent} to see if it’s interactable or not. This is how you can tell which {THING:StructureActiveVent} you have selected from the menu.

The last thing you need to do is select the desired internal and external pressure, found near the top of the {THING:CircuitboardAdvAirlockControl} panel.
